Class Section

java.lang.Object
Section
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
public class Section
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable
This class represents the Section nodes. It responsible for receiving orders from the Shipping Center node, appending the Section number to the order, and then sending the order to the Shipping Dock node, after a brief pause. This class implements the Runnable interface, which defines one method, run().
Since:
10/12/2021
Author:
Tucker Dickson

    • Section

      public Section​(int sectionNum, SynchronizedBuffer inputBuffer, SynchronizedBuffer outputBuffer)
      This is the sole constructor for the Section class. It takes in three parameters, a double and two SynchronizedBuffers, and uses them to initialize sectionNum, inputBuffer, and outputBuffer, respectively.

      sectionNum - This double will be used to initialize sectionNum.

  • Method Details

    • run

      public void run()
      This method is declared in the Runnable interface. It is responsible for getting orders from the input buffer (shared with Shipping Center nodes), appending the Section number to the order, waiting between 0 and 5 seconds (random), and then putting the new order to the output buffer (shared with Shipping Dock nodes).
      Specified by:
      run in interface java.lang.Runnable
